# .understandignore — patterns for files/dirs to exclude from analysis
# Syntax: same as .gitignore (globs, # comments, ! negation, trailing / for dirs)
#
# Built-in defaults (always excluded unless negated):
#   node_modules/, .git/, dist/, build/, target/, *.lock, pnpm-lock.yaml,
#   images, fonts, media, *.min.js, *.map, .idea/, .vscode/, LICENSE, etc.
#
# Tuned for Tiki v2 by /understand: exclude runtime data + tooling noise so the
# graph focuses on actual source (frontend, Rust backend, shared types, framework
# commands, docs). Comment any line out to re-include that set.

# --- Tiki runtime workflow STATE (data, not architecture) ---
# 231 files: archived issue plans, release groupings, state.json, research notes.
# These are generated workflow artifacts, not code that embodies design.
.tiki/

# --- Plugin / tooling sidecar data ---
.automaker/
mempalace.yaml
entities.json

# --- Editor / agent config (settings, not source) ---
# Matches root .claude/ AND the packages/framework/.claude shadow mirror of
# commands (md5-identical duplicate of packages/framework/commands — would
# create duplicate nodes).
.claude/
.vs/

# --- Accidental Windows NUL artifact ---
nul

# --- Component stylesheets (styling, low architectural signal) ---
# 45 .css files. Comment this out if you want styling represented in the graph.
*.css
